{{Quote|Hello, Cularin! It is I, the beneficent Thurm Loogg, representative of the omnibenevolent Metatheran Cartel, and I am here to speak to you.|Thurm Loogg|<ref name="Wizards">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/livingforce/swlf20030821loog|text=Thurm Loogg Speaks}}</ref>}}
'''Thurm Loogg''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Caarite]] who served the [[Metatheran Cartel]]'s envoy to the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]] after [[Velin Wir]]. He headed the Cartel's offices on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]] and oversaw their mining operations on [[Tilnes]], but was more of a spokesman and facilitator than a true executive. The Cartel failed to keep Loogg updated on all their plans, and he was often unsure of what he was supposed to be doing. Loogg's primary concern was himself and his own pocketbook, and his actions taken on behalf of the Cartel usually furthered his own greed, and he was not beyond being immoral to satisfy it.<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

One of Loogg's first tasks in Cularin was to attempt to negotiate reestablishing offices on the surface of Cularin after Velin Wir's actions destroyed any trust the Cartel might have had. [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Barnab Chistor]] of [[Gadrin]] ordered a vote but, after a vote ended in a tie, ultimately refused his petition. Loogg than presented a [[Warship/Legends|warship]], the ''[[XP-38]]'', as a gift to the people of Cularin, claiming it as a gesture of goodwill, but probably was an attempt to buy his way back into their good graces.<ref name="AUP">{{LivingForce|An Uneasy Peace}}</ref>

During the [[SoroSuub Anniversary celebration, 31 BBY|Festival of 31 BBY]], to which Loogg assisted, the Metatheran Cartel disturbed the annual speech of [[SoroSuub Corporation/Legends|SoroSuub Corporation]] manager [[Miim Te'Suub]] by overimposing the Cartel's logo. Te'Suub was angry and heatedly discussed with Loogg. The debate was heated enough to require the mediation of diplomats and Jedi consuls.<ref name="BW">''[[Blown Away]]'' (as described in [https://web.archive.org/web/20021218152817/www.wizards.com/rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20010927b_transmissions&c=swlfc Transmissions From the Living Force Campaign] on the [[Wikipedia:Internet Archive#Wayback machine|Way back machine]])</ref>

==Personality and traits==
Thurm Loogg had the ingratiating whine and broad smile common to [[Caarite]]s, not seeming to realize that his overly solicitous manner caused the residents of Cularin to trust him even less. He consistently dressed in blue robes trimmed with red. He was frustrating to deal with, not listening to things he did not want to hear, and waving people off in mid-sentence. He only wanted things done his way, or not at all.<ref name="LFC" />

==Behind the scenes==
At [[Gen Con Game Fair 2001]], Loogg was played by [[August Hahn]].

